author: wcax.com
title: Moose seen in South Burlington neighborhood
text:
SOUTH BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) - Who needs to go into the wild to see a moose?
Police in South Burlington, Vermont, say they've received several calls about a moose in the Market Street area off of Dorset Street on Monday morning.
Police are advising drivers and residents to use caution and not approach the moose.
In Manchester, New Hampshire, a moose was seen running through one neighborhood, jumping over cars and into yards on Sunday morning.
Drivers have been warned about moose encounters this time of year, and there have been some accidents and one death reported in New Hampshire last month. The Vermont Fish and Wildlife Department says this is the peak of their breeding season.
